{"title_page": "Donato Sabia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Italian athlete}}\n{{Infobox athlete\n| headercolor =\n| name = Donato Sabia\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| nationality = [[Italy|Italian]]\n| sport = [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n| event = [[400 metres]]<br>[[800 metres]]\n| club = [[Pro Patria Milano]]\n| collegeteam =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1963|9|11}}\n| birth_place = [[Potenza]], [[Italy]]\n| residence = \n| coach=\n| death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2020|4|7|1963|9|11}}\n| death_place= [[Potenza]], [[Italy]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| weight = {{convert|65|kg|lb|abbr=on}} \n| pb = \n*400 m:\t45.73 (1984)\n*800 m: 1:43.88 (1984)\n| country = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Italy national athletics team|Italy]]\n| medaltemplates=\n{{MedalCount\n|[[European Athletics Indoor Championships|European Indoor Championships]]|1|0|0\n|[[Mediterranean Games]]|0|1|0\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Donato Sabia''' (11 September 1963 \u2013 7 April 2020) was an [[Italy|Italian]] middle distance runner who specialized in the [[800 metres]].\n\n==Biography==\nDonato Sabia was born in [[Potenza]] and won two medals, at senior level, at the [[International athletics championships and games|International athletics competitions]], one of these with [[Italy national relays team at the international athletics championships|national relay team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportolimpico.it/dmdocuments/MEDAGLIE_U_1908_2008.pdf|title=PODIO INTERNAZIONALE DAL 1908 AL 2008 - UOMINI|publisher=sportolimpico.it|accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref> He participated at two editions of the [[Summer Olympics]] (1984, 1988), reaching, in both cases, the [[Summer Olympics|Olympic]] 800 metres final; he had 17 caps in [[Italy national athletics team|national team]] from 1982 to 1988.\n\nHis personal best time was 1:43.88 minutes, achieved in June 1984 in [[Florence]].<ref>[http://digilander.libero.it/atleticaleggera/ALL-TIME/5.htm Italian all-time list, men's 800 metres (last updated for year 2000)]</ref> In the [[400 metres]] he had 45.73 seconds, achieved in June 1984 in [[Milan]].<ref>[http://digilander.libero.it/atleticaleggera/ALL-TIME/4.htm Italian all-time list, men's 400 metres (last updated for year 2000)]</ref>\n\nHe died on 7 April 2020 in San Carlo Hospital, in Potenza, from [[COVID-19]], having on 31 March 2020 also lost his father to the same disease.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus, morto Donato Sabia: fu due volte finalista alle Olimpiadi |url=https://www.corriere.it/sport/20_aprile_08/coronavirus-morto-donato-sabia-fu-due-volte-finalista-olimpiadi-cdac8e60-796d-11ea-afb4-c5f49a569528.shtml |publisher=Corriere Della Sera |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Achievements==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=60% style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Year !!Competition !!Venue !!Result !!Event !!time !!Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1983\n|align=left|[[1983 Mediterranean Games|Mediterranean Games]] \n|align=left|Casablanca, Morocco\n|bgcolor=silver|2nd\n|4 \u00d7 400 m relay\n|3:04.54\n|\n|-\n|align=left|[[1983 World Championships in Athletics|World Championships]] \n|align=left|Helsinki, Finland\n|5th\n|[[1983 World Championships in Athletics - Men's 4 x 400 metres relay|4 \u00d7 400 m relay]]\n|3:05.10\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1984\n|align=left|[[1984 European Indoor Championships in Athletics|European Indoor Championships]] \n|align=left|Gothenburg, Sweden\n|bgcolor=\"gold\" align=\"center\" | 1st\n|800 m\n|1:48.05\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athleticsdb.com/1984-european-indoor-athletics-championships.php|title=15th indoor european athletics championships 1984 Gothenburg Sweden|publisher=athleticsdb.com|accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=left|[[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] \n|align=left|Los Angeles, United States\n|align=\"center\" | 5th\n|[[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 800 metres|800 m]]\n|1:44.53\n|\n|-\n|1988\n|align=left|[[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] \n|align=left|Seoul, South Korea\n|align=\"center\" | 7th\n|[[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics - Men's 800 metres|800 m]]\n|1:48.03\n|<ref>He ran in a better crono (1:44.90= in semi-finals.</ref>\n|}\n\n==National titles==\nHe has won 6 times the individual [[Italian Athletics Championships|national championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportolimpico.it/attachments/article/224/CAMPIONI%20ITALIANI_UOMINI.pdf |title=\"CAMPIONATI \"ASSOLUTI\" ITALIANI SUL PODIO TRICOLORE \u2013 1906 2012 |publisher=sportolimpico.it |accessdate=1 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224064654/http://www.sportolimpico.it/attachments/article/224/CAMPIONI%20ITALIANI_UOMINI.pdf |archivedate=24 December 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/nc/itai.htm|title=ITALIAN INDOOR CHAMPIONSHIPS|publisher=gbrathletics.com|accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref>\n*1 win in the [[400 metres]] (1984)\n*3 wins in the [[800 metres]] (1983, 1984, 1988)\n*2 wins in the [[400 metres]] indoor (1983, 1988)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Athletics in Italy#800 metres|Italian all-time lists - 800 metres]]\n* [[Italy national relays team at the international athletics championships|Italy national relay team]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IAAF|9773}}\n* {{IOC profile|donato-sabia}}\n* {{Sports-Reference|sa/donato-sabia-1}}\n\n{{Italian Athletics Champions in men's 400 m}}\n{{Italian Athletics Champions in men's 800 m}}\n{{Footer Italy athletics team at the 1984 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Footer Italy athletics team at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sabia, Donato}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian male middle-distance runners]]\n[[Category:Italian male sprinters]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of Italy]]\n[[Category:People from Potenza]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Basilicata]]\n[[Category:World Athletics Championships athletes for Italy]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games silver medalists for Italy]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in athletics]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 1983 Mediterranean Games]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian athlete}}\n{{Infobox athlete\n| headercolor =\n| name = Donato Sabia\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| nationality = [[Italy|Italian]]\n| sport = [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n| event = [[400 metres]]<br>[[800 metres]]\n| club = [[Pro Patria Milano]]\n| collegeteam =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|mf=yes|1963|9|11}}\n| birth_place = [[Potenza]], [[Italy]]\n| residence = \n| coach=\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2020|4|7|1963|9|11}}\n| death_place= [[Potenza]], [[Italy]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| weight = {{convert|65|kg|lb|abbr=on}} \n| pb = \n*400 m:\t45.73 (1984)\n*800 m: 1:43.88 (1984)\n| country = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Italy national athletics team|Italy]]\n| medaltemplates=\n{{MedalCount\n|[[European Athletics Indoor Championships|European Indoor Championships]]|1|0|0\n|[[Mediterranean Games]]|0|1|0\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Donato Sabia''' (11 September 1963 \u2013 7 April 2020) was an [[Italy|Italian]] middle distance runner who specialized in the [[800 metres]].\n\n==Biography==\nDonato Sabia was born in [[Potenza]] and won two medals, at senior level, at the [[International athletics championships and games|International athletics competitions]], one of these with [[Italy national relays team at the international athletics championships|national relay team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportolimpico.it/dmdocuments/MEDAGLIE_U_1908_2008.pdf|title=PODIO INTERNAZIONALE DAL 1908 AL 2008 - UOMINI|publisher=sportolimpico.it|accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref> He participated at two editions of the [[Summer Olympics]] (1984, 1988), reaching, in both cases, the [[Summer Olympics|Olympic]] 800 metres final; he had 17 caps in [[Italy national athletics team|national team]] from 1982 to 1988.\n\nHis personal best time was 1:43.88 minutes, achieved in June 1984 in [[Florence]].<ref>[http://digilander.libero.it/atleticaleggera/ALL-TIME/5.htm Italian all-time list, men's 800 metres (last updated for year 2000)]</ref> In the [[400 metres]] he had 45.73 seconds, achieved in June 1984 in [[Milan]].<ref>[http://digilander.libero.it/atleticaleggera/ALL-TIME/4.htm Italian all-time list, men's 400 metres (last updated for year 2000)]</ref>\n\nHe died on 7 April 2020 in San Carlo Hospital, in Potenza, from [[COVID-19]], having on 31 March 2020 also lost his father to the same disease.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus, morto Donato Sabia: fu due volte finalista alle Olimpiadi |url=https://www.corriere.it/sport/20_aprile_08/coronavirus-morto-donato-sabia-fu-due-volte-finalista-olimpiadi-cdac8e60-796d-11ea-afb4-c5f49a569528.shtml |publisher=Corriere Della Sera |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Achievements==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=60% style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Year !!Competition !!Venue !!Result !!Event !!time !!Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1983\n|align=left|[[1983 Mediterranean Games|Mediterranean Games]] \n|align=left|Casablanca, Morocco\n|bgcolor=silver|2nd\n|4 \u00d7 400 m relay\n|3:04.54\n|\n|-\n|align=left|[[1983 World Championships in Athletics|World Championships]] \n|align=left|Helsinki, Finland\n|5th\n|[[1983 World Championships in Athletics - Men's 4 x 400 metres relay|4 \u00d7 400 m relay]]\n|3:05.10\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1984\n|align=left|[[1984 European Indoor Championships in Athletics|European Indoor Championships]] \n|align=left|Gothenburg, Sweden\n|bgcolor=\"gold\" align=\"center\" | 1st\n|800 m\n|1:48.05\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athleticsdb.com/1984-european-indoor-athletics-championships.php|title=15th indoor european athletics championships 1984 Gothenburg Sweden|publisher=athleticsdb.com|accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=left|[[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] \n|align=left|Los Angeles, United States\n|align=\"center\" | 5th\n|[[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 800 metres|800 m]]\n|1:44.53\n|\n|-\n|1988\n|align=left|[[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] \n|align=left|Seoul, South Korea\n|align=\"center\" | 7th\n|[[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics - Men's 800 metres|800 m]]\n|1:48.03\n|<ref>He ran in a better crono (1:44.90= in semi-finals.</ref>\n|}\n\n==National titles==\nHe has won 6 times the individual [[Italian Athletics Championships|national championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportolimpico.it/attachments/article/224/CAMPIONI%20ITALIANI_UOMINI.pdf |title=\"CAMPIONATI \"ASSOLUTI\" ITALIANI SUL PODIO TRICOLORE \u2013 1906 2012 |publisher=sportolimpico.it |accessdate=1 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224064654/http://www.sportolimpico.it/attachments/article/224/CAMPIONI%20ITALIANI_UOMINI.pdf |archivedate=24 December 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/nc/itai.htm|title=ITALIAN INDOOR CHAMPIONSHIPS|publisher=gbrathletics.com|accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref>\n*1 win in the [[400 metres]] (1984)\n*3 wins in the [[800 metres]] (1983, 1984, 1988)\n*2 wins in the [[400 metres]] indoor (1983, 1988)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Athletics in Italy#800 metres|Italian all-time lists - 800 metres]]\n* [[Italy national relays team at the international athletics championships|Italy national relay team]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IAAF|9773}}\n* {{IOC profile|donato-sabia}}\n* {{Sports-Reference|sa/donato-sabia-1}}\n\n{{Italian Athletics Champions in men's 400 m}}\n{{Italian Athletics Champions in men's 800 m}}\n{{Footer Italy athletics team at the 1984 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Footer Italy athletics team at the 1988 Su